{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01S9EwGjvgSpMBp9kKntthQZ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the setup. I need to:\n\n1. Create the `es-secure-settings` secret with S3/MinIO credentials for Elasticsearch keystore\n2. Configure the Elasticsearch pods to load the keystore from this secret (using `elasticsearch-keystore`)\n3. Check if the s3 plugin is installed\n4. Register the snapshot repository\n5. Create a snapshot\n\nThe key thing here is \"Do not place credentials in elasticsearch.yml or env vars\" - this means I need to use Elasticsearch's keystore mechanism.\n\nFor Elasticsearch, the secure settings are stored in the keystore (`elasticsearch.keystore`). The keystore keys for S3/MinIO would be:\n- `s3.client.default.access_key`\n- `s3.client.default.secret_key`\n\nThe Elasticsearch S3 repository plugin uses these settings. I can either run `elasticsearch-keystore add` commands directly on existing pods and reload secure settings via API, or I can use an init container to build the keystore from a secret before the Elasticsearch pod starts.\n\nSince the task references storing credentials in the `es-secure-settings` secret, I need to create that secret first with the S3 credentials, then use an init container approach to populate the keystore from it during pod initialization. source of truth for the credentials. I could either manually add them to the keystore on each pod using `kubectl exec` and then reload the settings, or use a more automated approach where an init container populates the keystore from the mounted secret—though that would require restarting the pods. Let me first check if the S3 plugin is actually installed, then decide on the best path forward.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2260,"cache_read_input_tokens":30480,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2260},"output_tokens":26,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"005bc948-7599-4a23-a366-be6cfbf4dfac","uuid":"07df3022-3036-4685-bad3-357c4ec1f6d8","request_id":"req_011CcQh1T3NaUHyvCMkJ2eZA"}
