ck the current s3 configuration to see what's already set up. The endpoint is a client-level setting that needs to be configured in elasticsearch.yml, not at the repository level. I'm wondering if there's a way to override it directly through the snapshot API, but looking at the Elasticsearch docs, most S3 settings are static and require a restart—though the secure credentials can be stored in the keystore.\n\nActually, I'm recalling that in Elasticsearch 8.x and later, the S3 repository plugin does support specifying the endpoint directly in the repository settings, which would allow per-repository configuration without needing to restart the cluster. So the `endpoint` parameter can actually be set directly in the repository settings, which means I can configure it per-repository without modifying elasticsearch.yml. Now I need to check whether `path_style_access` and `protocol` can also be specified at the repository level or if those need to stay in the client configuration. I should try two approaches: first attempt the repository setup without modifying elasticsearch.yml, then add path_style_access if needed. But I also need to verify the keystore actually contains the correct MinIO credentials—I can only see the key names, not their values, so I'll need to create a secret with the proper credentials and update the keystore on each pod before attempting to register the repository.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6178,"cache_read_input_tokens":37562,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6178},"output_tokens":34,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"005bc948-7599-4a23-a366-be6cfbf4dfac","uuid":"181c5ca4-9526-45a2-bece-bd08f18d2472","request_id":"req_011CcQhEG5fuVGpDdzV8DNwc"}
